    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Memory Leak in F1AP DU UE Context Management Functions\n\n### Summary\nSeveral F1AP DU UE context management functions were not properly freeing ASN.1 structures after encoding, causing memory leaks. This fix adds proper cleanup to prevent resource leaks.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_ue_context_management.c`: Added `ASN_STRUCT_FREE` calls to 5 functions that were missing ASN.1 structure cleanup:\n  - `DU_send_UE_CONTEXT_SETUP_RESPONSE`\n  - `DU_send_UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_REQUEST`\n  - `DU_send_UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_COMPLETE`\n  - `DU_send_UE_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_RESPONSE`\n  - `DU_send_UE_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_REQUIRED`\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy load with frequent UE context setup/modify/release operations, memory usage would gradually increase due to leaked ASN.1 structures. Symptoms include:\n- Gradually increasing memory consumption over time\n- Eventual OOM conditions under sustained load\n- Memory leak detection tools reporting unreleased ASN.1 structures\n\nThe issue can be observed by monitoring memory usage during extended F1AP testing scenarios with multiple UE attach/detach cycles.\n"
}